Presented by @backcountry x @simmsfishing
~
Video: @prestonhoffman_ for @teamflylords

node.title: Boundless Backyard: Your Guide to the Perfect Backyard Fishing Adventure

node.text: With living rooms across the country morphing into home gyms and workouts venturing into uncharted territory, we reached out to adaptive athlete, @nationalabilitycenter ambassador, and Backcountry partner Santiago Vega to see how he's staying in shape. Check out @svsanchago’s at-home workout routine for athletes of all abilities. #AdaptiveNation

Athletes Brooklyn Bell (@badgal_brooky) and Caroline Gleich (@carolinegleich) are no strangers to long days in the backcountry. They recently joined us at Backcountry HQ to talk about their must-have items for backcountry skiing. Watch the video, then visit our Explore blog to learn more about Caroline and Brooklyn and the gear they pack for a day on the hill.

NEWWW! The latest yip-worthy Trail and XC MTB drops from @santacruzbicycles and @julianabicycles are stacked with send-sational updates for both advanced riders and those new to the trails.

The Bronson and Roubion—twinning MTBs from sibling brands Santa Cruz and Juliana, respectively—have a new mixed-wheel setup ( 29er in front and 27.5” in the rear), boosting stability on downhill and feature riding, while maintaining playfulness. For a capable, cushy, do-it-all bike, look no further.

The Santa Cruz Blur and all-new Juliana Wilder—both XC bikes yet the Wilder comes with a trail-build—feature identical lightweight frames and all-new Superlight suspension design. Flow fast singletrack and feel confident on techy sections whether you're a seasoned rider or just getting started on the mountain.

Shop the new rides and other new colorways through the link in our bio!

#findyourbackcountry #newbikeday

We’re thrilled to introduce you to the newest members of our Breaking Trail Family: Pınar Ateş (@queerquechua) and So Sinopoulos-Lloyd (@cyberpunkecology) of Queer Nature (@queernature) and Agnes Vianzon (@agnesvianzon) of Eastern Sierra Conservation Corps (@easternsierracc) are becoming Trailbreakers in 2022! 

Breaking Trail is our initiative to build a more inclusive backcountry, and these #BackcountryTrailbreakers are working to make wilderness & natural resource education accessible, diversify the conservation workforce, and provide opportunities for the LGBTQ2+ community to learn ecological and earth-based skills.
